kyll/projects/2\">version 4.0</a>. I’ve <a href=\"https://github.com/mmistakes/made-mistakes-jekyll/issues/629\">cached the rendering of Liquid includes</a>…</p>","timeToRead":2,"frontmatter":{"title":"Faster Netlify builds","date":"2019-02-26T00:00:00.000Z","date_pretty":"February 26th, 2019","date_from_now":"a year ago","path":"/notes/faster-netlify-builds/","author":null,"excerpt":null,"image":null}}},{"node":{"id":"bc6f8fb1-35af-5c34-99d1-5e4547cf8fc6","excerpt":"<p>Lately I’ve been toying with the idea of migrating from <a href=\"https://jekyllrb.com/\"><strong>Jekyll</strong></a> to <a href=\"https://www.gatsbyjs.org/\"><strong>GatsbyJS</strong></a> (more on that in a future post). Initial tests look promising…</p>","timeToRead":5,"frontmatter":{"title":"Autumn refresh","date":"2018-11-12T00:00:00.000Z","date_pretty":"November 12th, 2018","date_from_now":"2 years ago","path":"/notes/autumn-refresh/","author":null,"excerpt":"Using CSS Grid Layout Module to redesign a Jekyll site and further improve performance and accessibility.","image":{"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"aspectRatio":1.8095238095238095,"src":"/static/1c19b29b80964c7354e5035533def8d5/ad579/autumn-refresh-feature.jpg","srcSet":"/static/1c19b29b80964c7354e5035533def8d5/5827c/autumn-refresh-feature.jpg 190w,\n/static/1c19b29b80964c7354e5035533def8d5/a4187/autumn-refresh-feature.jpg 380w,\n/static/1c19b29b80964c7354e5035533def8d5/ad579/autumn-refresh-feature.jpg 760w,\n/static/1c19b29b80964c7354e5035533def8d5/d0063/autumn-refresh-feature.jpg 1140w,\n/static/1c19b29b80964c7354e5035533def8d5/fdaf9/autumn-refresh-feature.jpg 1520w,\n/static/1c19b29b80964c7354e5035533def8d5/4fb49/autumn-refresh-feature.jpg 1920w","sizes":"(max-width: 760px) 100vw, 760px"}}}}}},{"node":{"id":"fb7f6734-66e5-5210-97d2-cadefc1806aa","excerpt":"<p>Not going to lie — I love <a href=\"/tag/jekyll/\">Jekyll</a>, but huge static sites like mine take forever to build. What used to take seconds now go on for over 3…</p>","timeToRead":24,"frontmatter":{"title":"How I'm using Jekyll in 2017","date":"2017-08-30T00:00:00.000Z","date_pretty":"August 30th, 2017","date_from_now":"3 years ago","path":"/articles/using-jekyll-2017/","author":null,"excerpt":"Lessons learned from building, optimizing, and deploying a huge static site powered by everyone's favorite SSG — Jekyll.","image":{"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"aspectRatio":1.7757009345794392,"src":"/static/bb06d9639778ce3db80e380aa614566e/ad579/using-jekyll-2017-feature.jpg","srcSet":"/static/bb06d9639778ce3db80e380aa614566e/5827c/using-jekyll-2017-feature.jpg 190w,\n/static/bb06d9639778ce3db80e380aa614566e/a4187/using-jekyll-2017-feature.jpg 380w,\n/static/bb06d9639778ce3db80e380aa614566e/ad579/using-jekyll-2017-feature.jpg 760w,\n/static/bb06d9639778ce3db80e380aa614566e/d0063/using-jekyll-2017-feature.jpg 1140w,\n/static/bb06d9639778ce3db80e380aa614566e/fdaf9/using-jekyll-2017-feature.jpg 1520w,\n/static/bb06d9639778ce3db80e380aa614566e/9352a/using-jekyll-2017-feature.jpg 1600w","sizes":"(max-width: 760px) 100vw, 760px"}}}}}},{"node":{"id":"d193a24c-d74c-5336-842a-a8aab26216e8","excerpt":"<p>While inspecting the markup of some syntax highlighted code blocks I noticed something I hadn’t before, <code class=\"language-text\">language-lexer</code> classes:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"html\"><pre class=\"language-html\"><code class=\"language-html\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>div</span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">class</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span>language-css highlighter-rouge<span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n  <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>pre</span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">class</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span>highlight<span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n    <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>code</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>.foo { color: red; }<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>code</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n  <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>pre</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>div</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span></code></pre></div>\n<p>This extra hook<sup id=\"fnref-1\"><a href=\"#fn-1\" class=\"footnote-ref\">1</a></sup> on the <code class=\"language-text\">&lt;div&gt;</code>…</p>","timeToRead":2,"frontmatter":{"title":"Styling language specific code blocks with Jekyll","date":"2017-05-16T00:00:00.000Z","date_pretty":"May 16th, 2017","date_from_now":"3 years ago","path":"/notes/styling-language-specific-code-blocks/","author":null,"excerpt":"Interesting styling possibilities with syntax highlighted code blocks.","image":null}}},{"node":{"id":"e9376214-3d1a-5cb9-98ae-0c32d4a2e2b0","excerpt":"<p>Below are the Jekyll starters I’ve developed and open sourced. Each theme contains the <code class=\"language-text\">_layouts</code>, <code class=\"language-text\">_includes</code>, Sass/CSS, JavaScript, and other sample files…</p>","timeToRead":4,"frontmatter":{"title":"Jekyll themes","date":"2017-03-30T00:00:00.000Z","date_pretty":"March 30th, 2017","date_from_now":"3 years ago","path":"/work/jekyll-themes/","author":null,"excerpt":"Open source Jekyll themes to help build a site or blog on GitHub Pages, Netlify, and more.","image":{"childImageSha